net.proteusframework.ui.miwt

Class HistoryElement

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.HistoryElement

  • public class HistoryElement
extends Object
    HistoryElement instances are used to populate a History object to hold the history of Components. The HistoryElement can hold the component or a the information necessary to construct a component.
    Author:
    Pat B. Double (double@i2rd.com)

      • HistoryElement

        public HistoryElement(boolean cacheEnable)
        Creates an instance with the given cache attribute. The createComponent must be overriden if this constructor is used.
        Parameters:
        cacheEnable - true if a component may be re-used, false if a new component must be called each time the element becomes the current history element.

    • Method Detail

      • close

        public void close()
           throws CannotCloseMIWTException
        Called when the component should be closed. Normally called when this HistoryElement instance is removed from the History. Only a cached component should be closed. Non-cached components will be closed when the history position is changed. After this method is called, the component is null and may not be available to be recreated depending on the subclass implementation. The default implementation will not be able to recreate a cached component.
        Throws:
        CannotCloseMIWTException - if the cached component cannot be closed.

      • createComponent

        protected Component createComponent()
        Creates the component for this element. If parameters are needed the subclass should store those and use accordingly. This method will not be called if cacheEnable is true and cacheComponent is not null.
        Returns:
        Component.

      • getComponent

        public Component getComponent()
        Get the Component for this element. If cacheEnable is false, returns the result from createComponent(). If cacheEnable is true, createComponent() is called when necessary.
        Returns:
        Component.

      • isCached

        public boolean isCached()
        Returns whether the Component is cached.
        Returns:
        true if the component is cached.
